WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:15.920
The Prince and the Popper by Mark Twain copyright black cat publishing

00:15.920 --> 00:29.160
About the Author Mark Twain was born in Florida Missouri in 1835.

00:29.160 --> 00:34.080
His real name was Samuel Langhorn Clemens.

00:34.080 --> 00:40.880
When he was a boy he lived in Hannibal, Missouri on the Mississippi River.

00:40.880 --> 00:46.840
Many of the adventures in his books are about his youth in Hannibal.

00:46.840 --> 00:53.600
In 1857 he worked as a pilot on a steamboat on the Mississippi River.

00:53.600 --> 00:59.480
In 1861 he went to California and his life changed there.

00:59.480 --> 01:06.280
He began writing stories for a San Francisco newspaper called The Morning Call.

01:06.280 --> 01:14.960
At this time he changed his real name, Samuel Clemens, to a pen name, Mark Twain.

01:14.960 --> 01:23.160
In 1867 he published his short story, The Celebrated Jumping Frog of Calaveras County.

01:23.160 --> 01:28.000
It was a big success and he became famous.

01:28.000 --> 01:31.480
He travelled to Hawaii and Europe.

01:31.480 --> 01:40.800
In 1870 Mark Twain married Olivia Levy Langdon and they had three daughters, Susan, Jean

01:40.800 --> 01:43.160
and Clara.

01:43.160 --> 01:47.840
He and his family lived happily in Hartford, Connecticut.

01:47.840 --> 01:51.240
Here he wrote his three great books.

01:51.240 --> 02:00.840
The Adventures of Tom Sawyer, 1876, Life on the Mississippi, 1883 and The Adventures

02:00.840 --> 02:05.920
of Huckleberry Finn, 1884.

02:05.920 --> 02:10.400
People everywhere liked his books.

02:10.400 --> 02:16.520
Later in his life Mark Twain had financial problems and he and his family moved to Europe

02:16.520 --> 02:18.720
for nine years.

02:18.720 --> 02:25.360
When his daughters Susie and Jean died he became a very unhappy man.

02:25.360 --> 02:32.120
He loved his wife very much and she died too in 1904.

02:32.120 --> 02:38.680
After her death he went to live in New York City and then in Reading, Connecticut.

02:38.680 --> 02:43.520
He died in 1910 at the age of 75.

02:43.520 --> 02:52.760
His other works include The Prince and the Popper, 1881, The Innocence Abroad, 1869,

02:52.760 --> 03:00.760
A Connecticut Yankee in King Arthur's Court, 1889 and many short stories.

03:00.760 --> 03:06.600
He was the first American writer to change the American way of writing with his simple

03:06.600 --> 03:12.680
and funny language.

03:12.680 --> 03:17.480
Chapter 1 The Popper

03:17.480 --> 03:24.760
In 1537 two boys were born on the same day in London.

03:24.760 --> 03:29.920
Tom Canty was born to a poor family of porpers.

03:29.920 --> 03:38.000
They lived in one room near Pudding Lane, a poor neighborhood near London Bridge.

03:38.000 --> 03:44.480
Another child said Tom's father when he saw the baby.

03:44.480 --> 03:47.480
Another mouth to feed.

03:47.480 --> 03:50.160
He was not happy.

03:50.160 --> 03:53.600
No one wanted Tom.

03:53.600 --> 03:59.520
The other baby was Edward Tudor, Prince of Wales.

03:59.520 --> 04:04.600
His father was Henry VIII, King of England.

04:04.600 --> 04:15.480
They lived at Westminster Palace, a Prince is born, a handsome Prince is born, cried everyone

04:15.480 --> 04:18.000
at Westminster Palace.

04:18.000 --> 04:26.040
Let's have a big celebration with fireworks and a banquet.

04:26.040 --> 04:29.280
My son is born.

04:29.280 --> 04:32.440
He hid the King happily.

04:32.440 --> 04:38.880
All of England was happy and celebrated the arrival of the baby Prince.

04:38.880 --> 04:46.720
13 years later Tom was begging for money on the streets of London.

04:46.720 --> 04:53.000
His clothes were old and full of holes and he had no shoes.

04:53.000 --> 04:56.440
He was thin and dirty.

04:56.440 --> 05:04.640
He lived with his mother, grandmother and two sisters, bet and nan.

05:04.640 --> 05:10.280
The children had no beds and slept on the cold floor.

05:10.280 --> 05:14.200
They were always hungry.

05:14.200 --> 05:19.680
Tom's father, John Canty, never did any work.

05:19.680 --> 05:25.120
He sent Tom out to beg every day of the year.

05:25.120 --> 05:31.360
Sometimes people felt sorry for Tom and gave him a little money.

05:31.360 --> 05:36.560
But other times he did not get anything.

05:36.560 --> 05:41.920
When he did not bring any money home, his father hid him.

05:42.920 --> 05:50.120
I don't want to always be poor, thought Tom.

05:50.120 --> 05:58.640
I want to learn to read and write and I want to know about the world.

05:58.640 --> 06:04.880
Father Andrew was a kind old priest with white hair.

06:04.880 --> 06:11.360
He was Tom's friend and lived in the same building.

06:11.360 --> 06:14.920
Can you help me Father Andrew?

06:14.920 --> 06:17.120
Tom asked.

06:17.120 --> 06:28.120
I want to read and write and I want to speak good English like princes and important people.

06:28.120 --> 06:31.120
I can help you Tom.

06:31.120 --> 06:33.240
Said Father Andrew.

06:33.240 --> 06:37.360
Come to my room every day.

06:37.360 --> 06:43.360
He taught Tom to read and write and he taught him Latin.

06:43.360 --> 06:47.960
He told him stories about kings and princes.

06:47.960 --> 06:53.960
Tom learnt quickly and soon read Father Andrew's books.

06:53.960 --> 07:00.320
At night he often dreamed about the people in those books.

07:00.320 --> 07:06.200
When Tom was with other boys, he liked playing at being a prince.

07:06.200 --> 07:13.520
The other boys laughed at him and called him Prince Tom, but they liked him.

07:13.520 --> 07:18.040
They jumped in the mud and swam in the river.

07:18.040 --> 07:22.320
One day, Father Andrew said,

07:22.320 --> 07:28.720
Tom, why don't you go to Westminster Palace and see the real prince?

07:28.720 --> 07:32.240
He said, is the king's son?

07:32.240 --> 07:38.800
Perhaps you can see him at the palace.

07:38.800 --> 07:45.080
Chapter 2 The pauper meets the prince.

07:45.080 --> 07:53.080
The next morning Tom went to Westminster Palace and stood outside the big gate.

07:53.080 --> 07:56.800
There were two tall soldiers there.

07:56.800 --> 08:03.240
He looked at the splendid palace, but he could not go near it.

08:03.240 --> 08:10.600
He went back the next day and saw important ladies and gentlemen going to the palace,

08:10.600 --> 08:14.400
but he never saw the prince.

08:14.400 --> 08:22.120
Then one day he went back there again and saw a boy in very fine clothes.

08:23.120 --> 08:26.200
That looks like the prince.

08:26.200 --> 08:31.560
Thought Tom excitedly, he ran to the gate.

08:31.560 --> 08:34.200
You can't come in here.

08:34.200 --> 08:38.880
The soldiers cried and hit Tom.

08:38.880 --> 08:43.480
The prince saw this and did not like it.

08:43.480 --> 08:46.040
Why did you hit the poor boy?

08:46.040 --> 08:48.160
Asked Edward.

08:48.160 --> 08:51.000
Open the gates and bring him in.

08:51.000 --> 08:52.240
But sir.

08:52.240 --> 08:53.600
Said the soldier.

08:53.600 --> 08:56.520
He's only a dirty beggar.

08:56.520 --> 09:01.160
My father is the king of rich people and poor people.

09:01.160 --> 09:03.960
Answered Edward.

09:03.960 --> 09:08.800
The soldiers opened the gate and brought Tom in.

09:08.800 --> 09:10.560
Come with me.

09:10.560 --> 09:13.160
Edward said kindly.

09:13.160 --> 09:21.040
He took Tom inside the big palace with its long stairs and beautiful rooms.

09:21.040 --> 09:25.920
When they reached the prince's rooms, Edward called a servant.

09:25.920 --> 09:27.400
Bring food.

09:27.400 --> 09:32.600
He ordered meat, bread and fruit.

09:32.600 --> 09:38.160
Tom was very hungry and he ate the food quickly.

09:38.160 --> 09:39.240
Now.

09:39.240 --> 09:41.680
Said the prince smiling.

09:41.680 --> 09:43.880
What's your name?

09:43.880 --> 09:46.640
Where do you live?

09:46.640 --> 09:53.840
My name's Tom Canty and I live with my family in a room near Pudding Lane.

09:53.840 --> 09:55.760
In one room?

09:55.760 --> 09:57.520
Said the prince.

09:57.520 --> 10:00.640
Do you all live in one room?

10:00.640 --> 10:02.000
Yes.

10:02.000 --> 10:03.840
Said Tom.

10:03.840 --> 10:06.560
There are hundreds of rooms here.

10:06.560 --> 10:08.160
Said the prince.

10:08.160 --> 10:11.080
I have five rooms.

10:11.080 --> 10:13.440
We are very poor.

10:13.440 --> 10:15.440
Said Tom.

10:15.440 --> 10:20.600
My father doesn't work and I have to beg for money.

10:20.600 --> 10:24.720
When I don't bring money home, he hits me.

10:24.720 --> 10:27.640
Oh, your father hits you.

10:27.640 --> 10:29.160
Said the prince.

10:29.160 --> 10:34.240
I'll send my soldiers to your house and they'll put him in prison.

10:34.240 --> 10:36.920
No, no, please sir.

10:36.920 --> 10:38.520
Said Tom.

10:38.520 --> 10:42.040
Think of my mother and sisters.

10:42.040 --> 10:44.040
I understand.

10:44.040 --> 10:46.680
Said the prince kindly.

10:46.680 --> 10:52.440
I have two sisters, Lady Elizabeth and Lady Mary.

10:52.440 --> 10:58.240
Lady Elizabeth is very nice, but I don't like Lady Mary.

10:58.240 --> 11:01.960
She never laughs or smiles.

11:01.960 --> 11:06.560
I also have a cousin, Lady Jane Grey.

11:06.560 --> 11:10.240
She's my age and is very kind.

11:10.240 --> 11:13.520
But I don't know any boys.

11:13.520 --> 11:15.960
Do you play with other boys?

11:15.960 --> 11:18.000
Of course I do.

11:18.000 --> 11:19.840
Said Tom.

11:19.840 --> 11:21.480
I don't.

11:21.480 --> 11:24.640
Said the prince, sadly.

11:24.640 --> 11:26.640
What do you play?

11:26.640 --> 11:31.440
We play by the river, swim, and jump in the mud.

11:31.440 --> 11:33.480
Said Tom.

11:33.480 --> 11:40.440
Sometimes we play princes and soldiers, and other times we play ball.

11:40.440 --> 11:45.000
We dance and sing and make a lot of noise too.

11:45.000 --> 11:48.240
We always have great fun.

11:48.240 --> 11:56.800
I want to play by the river and swim and jump in the mud once in my life, but I can't because

11:56.800 --> 11:58.840
I'm a prince.

11:58.840 --> 12:01.640
Said Edward, sadly.

12:01.640 --> 12:08.680
He looked out of the window and then said suddenly, I've got an idea.

12:08.680 --> 12:10.720
Look in the mirror.

12:10.720 --> 12:17.480
You and I are the same, you're like me and I'm like you.

12:17.480 --> 12:20.520
The two boys were both thin.

12:20.520 --> 12:29.320
They had the same brown hair, the same brown eyes, the same nose, the same mouth and the

12:29.320 --> 12:31.600
same voice.

12:31.600 --> 12:34.640
They were also the same height.

12:34.640 --> 12:37.840
They were almost identical.

12:37.840 --> 12:39.680
The prince was excited.

12:39.680 --> 12:42.720
Let's change clothes.

12:42.720 --> 12:47.600
You'll be the prince and I'll be the porper for a short time.

12:47.600 --> 12:52.000
It'll be a game, a wonderful game.

12:52.000 --> 12:56.360
Take off those old clothes and put on my clothes.

12:56.360 --> 13:00.960
We can both be happy for a short time.

13:00.960 --> 13:07.000
Tom washed his face and put on the prince's elegant clothes.

13:07.000 --> 13:12.440
Then Edward put on Tom's dirty old trousers and shirt.

13:12.440 --> 13:17.200
Now Edward was Tom and Tom was Edward.

13:17.200 --> 13:24.320
They looked at each other in the big mirror and laughed loudly.

13:24.320 --> 13:26.840
Stay here until I come back.

13:26.840 --> 13:29.040
Said the prince happily.

13:29.040 --> 13:32.640
I want to be a porper for an hour.

13:32.640 --> 13:39.720
I'm going to swim in the river and jump in the mud with the other boys.

13:39.720 --> 13:44.960
Before leaving, he took something big and round from the table.

13:44.960 --> 13:52.320
He went to a corner of the room and put it inside an old Italian suit of armour.

13:52.320 --> 13:55.160
Then he ran out of the door.

13:56.040 --> 13:58.520
But what will I do?

13:58.520 --> 14:00.920
Tom asked himself.

14:04.280 --> 14:06.280
Chapter 3.

14:06.280 --> 14:09.720
Changing Places

14:09.720 --> 14:13.400
The prince went to the gates of the palace.

14:13.400 --> 14:16.360
Open the palace gates quickly.

14:16.360 --> 14:18.520
He ordered.

14:18.520 --> 14:23.800
The soldiers opened the gates and Edward went out.

14:23.800 --> 14:27.880
One of the soldiers hit him on the head.

14:27.880 --> 14:33.000
Don't give orders to the king's soldiers, boy.

14:33.000 --> 14:36.600
Edward fell to the ground and said,

14:36.600 --> 14:38.680
I'm Prince Edward.

14:38.680 --> 14:40.600
Prince of Wales.

14:40.600 --> 14:44.440
Well, then I'm the king of England.

14:44.440 --> 14:47.160
Said the soldier laughing.

14:47.160 --> 14:50.360
You can go to prison for that.

14:50.360 --> 14:53.080
Said Edward angrily.

14:53.080 --> 14:55.560
His face was red.

14:55.560 --> 14:59.160
The crowd laughed loudly and said,

14:59.160 --> 15:03.560
He was bad.

15:03.560 --> 15:07.880
Edward walked down the road angrily.

15:07.880 --> 15:10.920
He forgot about playing by the river

15:10.920 --> 15:14.920
and walked in the streets of London.

15:14.920 --> 15:18.920
This was his first walk in the city.

15:18.920 --> 15:23.080
He was soon lost and tired.

15:23.080 --> 15:27.720
His feet hurt a lot because he had no shoes

15:27.720 --> 15:32.200
and his stomach hurt because he was hungry.

15:32.200 --> 15:35.240
I must go back to the palace.

15:35.240 --> 15:37.080
He thought.

15:37.080 --> 15:39.960
He stopped people and said,

15:39.960 --> 15:43.720
Show me the way to Westminster Palace.

15:43.800 --> 15:49.640
He never said, Please, because he was the prince.

15:49.640 --> 15:54.040
Some people laughed at him and others were angry

15:54.040 --> 15:57.240
because he was not polite.

15:57.240 --> 16:00.600
But no one helped him.

16:00.600 --> 16:04.120
This is terrible, he thought.

16:04.120 --> 16:10.520
I'm hungry and cold and I don't know where to sleep tonight.

16:10.600 --> 16:13.560
Tom's house is near Pudding Lane.

16:13.560 --> 16:18.200
Perhaps Tom's mother and sisters will help me.

16:18.680 --> 16:24.200
Edward walked for a long time in the dark, dirty streets.

16:24.200 --> 16:27.960
There was a bad smell everywhere.

16:27.960 --> 16:32.680
Then it started to rain and it was cold.

16:32.680 --> 16:35.640
Edward was unhappy.

16:35.640 --> 16:40.280
Suddenly he felt a big heavy hand around his arm.

16:41.800 --> 16:46.120
What are you doing out at this time, Tom Canty?

16:47.480 --> 16:49.000
Asked a big man.

16:50.200 --> 16:53.160
Where's the money from your day's work?

16:54.040 --> 16:56.440
Ouch! You're hurting me.

16:57.080 --> 16:58.280
Cried Edward.

16:59.240 --> 17:00.840
Are you his father?

17:01.640 --> 17:02.600
His father?

17:03.560 --> 17:06.440
I'm your father, you stupid boy.

17:07.240 --> 17:10.120
Said John Canty, hitting Edward.

17:10.840 --> 17:12.120
No! No!

17:13.240 --> 17:14.280
Cried Edward.

17:15.480 --> 17:18.440
I'm Edward, the Prince of Wales.

17:19.480 --> 17:22.040
Your son is in Westminster Palace.

17:22.920 --> 17:27.240
He's wearing my clothes and I'm wearing his clothes.

17:28.280 --> 17:29.640
We changed places.

17:30.600 --> 17:31.640
It was a game.

17:32.840 --> 17:34.200
Take me to the palace.

17:36.040 --> 17:40.760
John Canty looked at the boy with cold eyes and said,

17:41.400 --> 17:43.720
You're mad, mad.

17:45.240 --> 17:49.320
He took Edward's arm and pulled him down the road.

17:50.440 --> 17:58.920
You're coming home with me and tomorrow morning you can start work early and bring some money home.

17:59.400 --> 18:03.640
At the palace, Tom was alone in the prince's room.

18:05.080 --> 18:11.800
He looked at himself in the big mirror on the wall and liked his new clothes.

18:12.760 --> 18:16.520
He looked at all the beautiful things around him.

18:17.560 --> 18:22.280
Pictures of kings, queens, princes and princesses.

18:23.160 --> 18:25.480
Lovely chairs and tables.

18:26.120 --> 18:31.560
Beautiful glasses and cups and big plates full of fruit.

18:32.760 --> 18:36.680
He touched the princess sword and played with it for a while.

18:37.640 --> 18:42.760
He was happy in the prince's room and liked playing this new game.

18:44.280 --> 18:50.200
But after an hour, he was tired of it and he began to feel afraid.

18:50.680 --> 18:52.760
Where is the real prince?

18:53.480 --> 18:57.000
He thought, why isn't he back?

18:57.880 --> 18:59.880
I must look for him.

19:01.400 --> 19:05.560
He opened a big door and saw four gentlemen.

19:06.520 --> 19:08.520
They bowed to Tom.

19:09.640 --> 19:14.120
Oh, cried Tom and shut the door quickly.

19:14.760 --> 19:17.720
Cried Tom and shut the door quickly.

19:18.600 --> 19:19.960
How strange!

19:20.680 --> 19:22.440
One gentleman said.

19:22.440 --> 19:24.600
The prince is probably ill.

19:25.880 --> 19:28.760
Let's call his sisters or Lady Jane.

19:29.720 --> 19:31.320
Said the second gentleman.

19:32.920 --> 19:37.080
A beautiful young woman with a kind face opened the door.

19:38.440 --> 19:40.520
It was Lady Jane Grey.

19:41.400 --> 19:44.760
Tom was afraid and went down on his knees.

19:46.040 --> 19:48.440
Please save me, kind Lady.

19:49.240 --> 19:50.200
Said Tom.

19:51.080 --> 19:53.160
I'm not Prince Edward.

19:53.640 --> 19:57.720
My name's Tom Canty and I'm a porper.

19:58.280 --> 20:01.400
Prince Edward and I change clothes.

20:02.120 --> 20:08.280
He's wearing my dirty old clothes and I'm wearing his beautiful clothes.

20:08.600 --> 20:14.280
Please find the prince so I can get my clothes back.

20:16.440 --> 20:18.920
Oh dear, you're ill Edward.

20:20.040 --> 20:21.160
Lady Jane said.

20:23.640 --> 20:24.920
Please come with me.

20:25.800 --> 20:27.800
Your father wants to see you.

20:29.880 --> 20:33.320
My father is John Canty here.

20:33.960 --> 20:35.160
Ask Tom.

20:36.840 --> 20:39.480
Lady Jane did not answer him.

20:41.640 --> 20:43.560
The king is very ill.

20:44.680 --> 20:46.120
She said sadly.

20:47.720 --> 20:50.280
Tom followed her to the king's bedroom.

20:52.120 --> 20:55.800
King Henry was in bed and his face was white.

20:58.440 --> 21:00.920
Here is your son, your Majesty.

21:01.880 --> 21:03.480
Said Lady Jane.

21:05.000 --> 21:09.080
The king opened his eyes and smiled at Tom.

21:10.600 --> 21:12.360
What's the matter, Edward?

21:13.320 --> 21:14.280
Tell your father.

21:15.800 --> 21:17.160
Are you the king?

21:18.280 --> 21:19.080
Ask Tom.

21:19.880 --> 21:22.440
Looking at the big fat man.

21:23.480 --> 21:25.080
Of course I'm the king.

21:26.120 --> 21:27.720
Don't you know your father?

21:29.320 --> 21:30.360
Tom bowed.

21:31.720 --> 21:34.680
Sir, I'm not your son.

21:34.680 --> 21:36.600
I'm not the prince.

21:36.600 --> 21:38.840
I'm poor Tom.

21:38.840 --> 21:40.840
Stop this nonsense.

21:40.840 --> 21:42.840
Said King Henry.

21:43.320 --> 21:48.440
You are the prince and you will be king when I die.

21:49.080 --> 21:52.840
Now go and rest before the banquet tonight.

21:53.480 --> 21:56.200
There'll be a lot of important men.

21:56.440 --> 22:03.480
Tom and Lady Jane went back to the prince's room.

22:05.080 --> 22:09.800
After a short time, Lord Hartford went to see King Henry.

22:11.640 --> 22:16.040
Lord Hartford was a short fat man with a long nose.

22:17.320 --> 22:19.800
He was the king's first lord.

22:21.400 --> 22:22.200
Lord Hartford.

22:22.920 --> 22:23.560
Said the king.

22:24.440 --> 22:28.840
I'm very ill, but I must continue working.

22:30.040 --> 22:33.000
I have to read and sign many papers.

22:34.200 --> 22:36.360
Where is the great seal?

22:37.080 --> 22:40.040
You gave it to Prince Edward two days ago.

22:40.920 --> 22:42.200
Said Lord Hartford.

22:43.400 --> 22:44.600
I'll go and get it.

22:46.920 --> 22:51.880
Lord Hartford came back without the great seal and he was worried.

22:52.760 --> 22:59.560
Your Majesty, he said, the prince can't remember where it is or what it is.

23:00.760 --> 23:02.520
He can't remember.

23:03.720 --> 23:05.320
Then he really is ill.

23:06.600 --> 23:09.480
The great seal is very important.

23:11.080 --> 23:13.000
Let's wait until he's better.

23:15.400 --> 23:19.400
At one o'clock that afternoon, Tom had lunch.

23:19.480 --> 23:25.960
He was surprised when he saw the royal dining room with its gold furniture.

23:27.160 --> 23:30.840
Several servants stood near him while he ate.

23:31.800 --> 23:35.160
Poor Tom made a lot of mistakes that afternoon,

23:35.720 --> 23:39.480
but no one laughed because they thought he was ill.

23:40.200 --> 23:44.600
He ate with his fingers and made noises with his mouth.

23:45.880 --> 23:49.080
Then he looked at his napkin and said,

23:49.400 --> 23:50.600
with great interest.

23:53.240 --> 23:55.960
Please take this lovely napkin away.

23:57.080 --> 23:59.800
I don't want to make it dirty.

24:01.880 --> 24:05.720
Then he took a lot of nuts and put them in his pockets.

24:07.480 --> 24:11.160
At the end of the meal, a servant brought a finger bowl.

24:12.760 --> 24:15.480
But Tom did not clean his fingers in it.

24:16.760 --> 24:18.120
He drank from it.

24:19.400 --> 24:24.360
King Henry VIII

24:27.560 --> 24:33.400
In the story you are reading, King Henry VIII is Prince Edward's father.

24:34.600 --> 24:43.560
He was one of England's most famous kings and ruled from 1509 to 1547.

24:45.320 --> 24:48.520
Who was King Henry VIII and what did he do?

24:49.720 --> 24:52.200
Young Henry

24:54.680 --> 25:00.760
Henry VIII was born on the 28th of June 1491.

25:02.040 --> 25:07.480
He was a tall, good-looking man with red hair and blue eyes.

25:08.840 --> 25:12.840
He liked playing tennis, hunting and riding horses.

25:14.040 --> 25:17.480
He also liked reading, music and dancing.

25:18.440 --> 25:25.960
He was an intelligent man and spoke English, French, Spanish and Latin.

25:28.360 --> 25:34.920
Henry became king when he was almost 18 and married Catherine of Aragon.

25:36.280 --> 25:39.560
She was the daughter of King Ferdinand of Spain.

25:41.080 --> 25:44.360
They were happy together for almost 20 years.

25:44.360 --> 25:51.320
During Henry's reign, the Renaissance developed in England.

25:52.760 --> 25:59.640
There were always many writers, poets, painters and musicians at his court.

26:01.000 --> 26:09.240
The young king lived in beautiful castles and palaces and wore expensive clothes and jewels.

26:09.240 --> 26:17.240
King Henry wanted a son, but Catherine could not give him one.

26:18.760 --> 26:25.560
During his 20 years of marriage, four sons were born, but they all died.

26:27.000 --> 26:31.000
Only a daughter called Princess Mary survived.

26:32.360 --> 26:36.600
The king wanted a son to become king after his death.

26:40.200 --> 26:42.280
Henry meets Anne Boleyn.

26:44.440 --> 26:48.600
In 1526, Henry met Anne Boleyn.

26:49.880 --> 26:54.600
She was a young English woman with dark hair and dark eyes.

26:55.880 --> 26:59.560
Henry fell in love with her and wanted to marry her.

27:00.760 --> 27:02.360
He wanted a son from her.

27:03.320 --> 27:11.640
He decided to divorce Catherine, but he was Catholic and he needed permission from the Pope in Rome.

27:12.920 --> 27:18.440
The Pope did not give him permission and Henry was very angry.

27:20.520 --> 27:28.120
In 1533, he chose a new Archbishop of Canterbury called Thomas Cranmer.

27:29.000 --> 27:32.920
Cranmer believed in the complete power of the king.

27:34.040 --> 27:38.120
Soon, he helped to establish the Church of England.

27:39.240 --> 27:44.840
This church had different rooms and Henry was able to divorce Catherine.

27:46.840 --> 27:52.280
Henry and Anne Boleyn were secretly married and Catherine left the court.

27:52.280 --> 27:59.960
In May 1533, Anne gave birth to Princess Elizabeth.

28:01.160 --> 28:05.720
Henry was unhappy with Anne because she did not give him a son.

28:07.080 --> 28:14.120
However, Princess Elizabeth later became a great queen. Queen Elizabeth the first.

28:17.000 --> 28:18.040
Jane Seymour

28:18.040 --> 28:24.200
When Henry met Jane Seymour, he fell in love with her.

28:25.400 --> 28:30.280
He was a friend of her father, Sir John Seymour of Wiltshire,

28:31.000 --> 28:33.400
and met her at her father's house.

28:34.920 --> 28:37.560
He also thought she could give him a son.

28:39.400 --> 28:45.480
Henry accused Anne of treason and she was beheaded in 1536.

28:45.800 --> 28:55.640
Henry soon married Jane Seymour and in 1537, Jane gave birth to a son, Prince Edward.

28:56.760 --> 29:01.160
King Henry was very happy and everyone in England celebrated.

29:01.960 --> 29:04.520
The king finally had a son.

29:06.120 --> 29:11.800
But Queen Jane died 12 days later and Henry was very sad.

29:12.760 --> 29:18.520
Prince Edward had the best teachers and received an excellent education.

29:20.920 --> 29:27.960
During this time, Henry built beautiful palaces, castles and homes around England.

29:29.160 --> 29:32.440
One of these was Deal Castle in Kent.

29:34.040 --> 29:40.680
Henry built many warships and England soon had the strongest navy in Europe.

29:42.600 --> 29:45.720
Political problems

29:48.040 --> 29:51.240
Spain and France were Henry's enemies.

29:52.280 --> 30:00.200
He needed a strong ally, so he decided to marry a German princess called Anne of Cleves.

30:01.800 --> 30:08.680
The royal painter Hans Holbein went to Germany to paint a portrait of Anne of Cleves.

30:08.760 --> 30:16.440
Henry liked her portrait, but when she arrived in England, he was surprised because she was

30:16.440 --> 30:22.440
ugly and didn't speak English. Henry married her for political reasons

30:23.160 --> 30:26.280
and then divorced her a few months later.

30:29.320 --> 30:30.280
Health problems

30:32.280 --> 30:38.440
In 1540, Henry was 49 and he had serious health problems.

30:39.560 --> 30:42.680
He was very fat and could not walk well.

30:44.040 --> 30:50.440
Soon after divorcing Anne of Cleves, he married a pretty girl of 19 years old

30:50.440 --> 30:57.960
called Catherine Howard. But because she had relationships with other men, Henry accused her

30:57.960 --> 31:06.520
of treason. She was beheaded in 1542. The Last Queen

31:08.760 --> 31:19.080
Henry married his sixth and last queen in 1543. Her name was Catherine Parr and she was a quiet,

31:19.080 --> 31:26.440
well-educated woman. She looked after Henry's three children, Mary, Elizabeth and Edward.

31:27.320 --> 31:33.160
She was kind to them and was interested in their education. Henry was happy with her.

31:33.480 --> 31:40.680
During Henry's last years, he could not walk and servants carried him everywhere.

31:41.800 --> 31:44.520
He also had very bad headaches.

31:45.800 --> 31:55.960
Catherine looked after him lovingly. Henry died on the 28th of January 1547 at the age of 55.

31:56.840 --> 32:02.520
He was buried at Windsor next to his favourite wife, Jane Seymour.

32:06.840 --> 32:09.560
Chapter 4 The Guildhall

32:12.040 --> 32:16.120
There were long steps from Westminster Palace to the River Thames.

32:17.560 --> 32:20.520
Soldiers stored on both sides of the steps.

32:20.680 --> 32:26.840
The people of London were near the river looking at the Royal Barge.

32:28.520 --> 32:31.800
When Tom came out, the crowd shouted,

32:32.760 --> 32:35.000
Long live Prince Edward!

32:37.400 --> 32:42.600
Tom wore beautiful white clothes and jewels for the important banquet.

32:44.200 --> 32:48.920
He looked at the river and thought about his friends and his games.

32:50.680 --> 32:56.760
He walked down the stairs to the Royal Barge and the lords and ladies bowed.

32:58.360 --> 33:04.520
Tom stood at the front of the barge as it moved slowly down the river to the Guildhall.

33:05.960 --> 33:10.280
He was excited because everything was new to him.

33:12.120 --> 33:19.240
The Guildhall was a big building near the river where all the rich and important men of London

33:19.320 --> 33:27.000
were waiting for the prince. At the same time, John Canty took Edward

33:27.000 --> 33:33.160
and pulled him down Pudding Lane. People laughed and followed them.

33:34.680 --> 33:39.800
Teach that boy a lesson! shouted a young woman.

33:41.720 --> 33:47.720
When they came near John Canty's house, Father Andrew stood in front of them.

33:48.360 --> 33:51.320
Don't hurt him! Let him go!

33:52.600 --> 33:54.040
Said Father Andrew.

33:55.880 --> 34:04.360
John Canty was angry and did not answer him. He hit Father Andrew on the head with a stick

34:04.360 --> 34:09.800
and he fell to the ground. John Canty pulled Edward home.

34:11.160 --> 34:15.640
He opened the door of his small room and said to his wife,

34:16.280 --> 34:24.600
Here is your dear son. He doesn't have a penny for us and he's mad too.

34:26.840 --> 34:29.800
Tom's mother ran to Edward and said,

34:31.160 --> 34:37.160
Oh my poor boy! No money, no food.

34:38.360 --> 34:43.240
Said John Canty to Edward and he pushed him to the floor.

34:43.480 --> 34:50.680
Tom's father was a cruel man. There was a voice outside the door.

34:51.640 --> 34:54.840
John Canty, quick, open the door.

34:55.720 --> 34:56.760
What's the matter?

34:57.560 --> 34:58.440
Said Canty.

34:59.000 --> 35:03.960
You hit Father Andrew on the head and now he's dead.

35:05.080 --> 35:06.200
Said a young man.

35:07.160 --> 35:07.560
Dead?

35:08.520 --> 35:10.120
Asked John Canty.

35:11.080 --> 35:16.120
This is bad. A lot of people saw me when I hit the old man.

35:17.800 --> 35:20.120
He turned to his wife and said,

35:21.080 --> 35:26.920
Quick, take the girls and meet me at London Bridge.

35:28.200 --> 35:30.600
I'll take another road with the boy.

35:31.160 --> 35:37.480
Canty took Edward by the arm and pulled him through the small,

35:37.480 --> 35:41.160
dark streets until they came to the river.

35:42.360 --> 35:45.160
There he saw a crowd of people.

35:45.960 --> 35:49.320
Some of them were sitting at tables and drinking.

35:50.360 --> 35:51.640
What's all this?

35:52.280 --> 35:53.880
Canty asked a man.

35:54.760 --> 35:56.360
What are you waiting for?

35:57.240 --> 35:58.760
Don't you know?

35:59.400 --> 36:00.280
Said the man.

36:01.160 --> 36:05.400
We're waiting to see Prince Edward in the Royal Barge.

36:06.280 --> 36:09.480
He's going to a banquet at the Guild Hall.

36:10.600 --> 36:12.360
Here, have a drink.

36:14.600 --> 36:17.400
He gave John Canty a big cup.

36:18.760 --> 36:23.240
Canty removed his hand from Edward's arm to pick up the cup.

36:23.240 --> 36:28.280
Edward quickly ran away between the men's legs.

36:29.720 --> 36:31.000
Canty looked down.

36:31.800 --> 36:35.720
Where's the boy? Stop in. Catch him.

36:37.160 --> 36:39.320
Edward ran away and thought,

36:40.120 --> 36:43.480
I must go to the Guild Hall and find Tom.

36:44.120 --> 36:46.360
Then we can change clothes again.

36:48.520 --> 36:52.920
When Tom came into the Guild Hall, everyone stood up

36:53.320 --> 36:54.120
and bowed.

36:55.560 --> 37:00.440
He sat at the high table with the prince's sisters and Lady Jane.

37:02.040 --> 37:05.960
Hundreds of servants brought in all kinds of food.

37:07.320 --> 37:13.320
There was a lot of meat, fish and cheese and many different cakes.

37:14.840 --> 37:16.680
Soon the banquet began.

37:17.880 --> 37:22.520
Everyone talked and laughed and there were singers and dancers.

37:24.200 --> 37:30.360
Tom was surprised by everything he saw and started to enjoy the Royal banquet.

37:32.360 --> 37:37.400
Edward finally reached the Guild Hall and he was tired and dirty.

37:38.760 --> 37:42.280
He went to one of the soldiers and cried,

37:42.280 --> 37:43.800
I'm Prince Edward.

37:44.600 --> 37:47.800
Open the doors. I want to come in.

37:48.920 --> 37:50.760
The soldier laughed at him.

37:51.480 --> 37:54.520
I order you to open the doors.

37:54.520 --> 37:55.240
He cried.

37:55.960 --> 37:57.160
Don't be a fool.

37:57.720 --> 37:58.680
Said the soldier.

37:59.960 --> 38:01.080
Stand back.

38:02.760 --> 38:05.160
The people in the crowd were angry.

38:07.480 --> 38:09.320
Send this boy away.

38:10.280 --> 38:11.160
They shouted.

38:11.720 --> 38:12.680
He's mad.

38:13.480 --> 38:17.400
We want to see the prince when the banquet finishes.

38:18.280 --> 38:19.960
Go away boy.

38:21.000 --> 38:22.440
I won't go away.

38:23.080 --> 38:25.240
I am Prince Edward.

38:26.040 --> 38:28.840
The boy in there is a pauper.

38:29.880 --> 38:32.600
I am the son of King Henry.

38:34.680 --> 38:40.040
The crowd began to look dangerous but Edward did not move.

38:41.800 --> 38:49.320
Then a tall man with black hair came out of the angry crowd and stood next to Edward.

38:50.120 --> 38:54.280
Perhaps you're a prince and perhaps you're not.

38:55.160 --> 38:55.960
Said the man.

38:56.840 --> 39:01.800
But you're a courageous boy and I like you so I'll help you.

39:03.000 --> 39:04.200
Who are you sir?

39:04.760 --> 39:05.720
Asked Edward.

39:06.680 --> 39:11.560
My name is Miles Hendon and I'm a soldier of the King of England.

39:12.600 --> 39:17.160
I returned from France yesterday and I'm going to my home in the country.

39:17.160 --> 39:21.080
The dangerous crowd came nearer.

39:21.640 --> 39:22.680
Stand back.

39:23.080 --> 39:25.400
Cried Miles to the crowd.

39:25.880 --> 39:29.320
He took out his sword and held it up.

39:29.560 --> 39:30.760
Kill them.

39:31.320 --> 39:34.520
Cried someone from the back of the crowd.

39:35.720 --> 39:38.680
People started to throw things at them.

39:39.160 --> 39:43.160
Miles stood in front of Edward and defended him.

39:43.160 --> 39:48.760
The crowd was big and angry and Miles was alone.

39:48.760 --> 39:53.320
Suddenly everyone stopped shouting and fighting.

39:53.320 --> 39:57.880
They heard the sound of horses and a soldier cried.

39:57.880 --> 39:59.720
I'll stand back.

39:59.720 --> 40:02.600
The king's first lord is coming.

40:02.600 --> 40:06.200
The soldiers pushed the crowd back.

40:06.200 --> 40:11.320
Lord Hartford ran up the stairs and went into the forest.

40:11.320 --> 40:15.400
He went to the stairs and went into the guild hall.

40:15.400 --> 40:18.440
He went to Tom and said.

40:18.440 --> 40:19.960
Your Majesty.

40:19.960 --> 40:21.400
I'm sorry.

40:21.400 --> 40:23.240
Your father is dead.

40:25.240 --> 40:28.200
Then he looked at the people and shouted.

40:28.760 --> 40:30.920
King Henry is dead.

40:31.880 --> 40:34.120
Long live King Edward.

40:35.880 --> 40:37.960
Everyone at the banquet shouted.

40:38.920 --> 40:41.400
Long live King Edward.

40:43.400 --> 40:47.640
Miles Hendon quickly took Edward's arm and they ran away.

40:52.040 --> 40:55.560
Chapter 5 Sir Miles

40:57.800 --> 41:01.160
Miles took Edward to an inn near London bridge.

41:02.360 --> 41:04.120
People in the streets shouted.

41:05.320 --> 41:07.240
King Henry is dead.

41:08.040 --> 41:10.040
Long live King Edward.

41:12.120 --> 41:17.320
Edward thought of his father and became very sad and started to cry.

41:18.760 --> 41:23.640
King Henry was a difficult man but he was always kind to him.

41:24.760 --> 41:26.680
And now he was dead.

41:28.520 --> 41:30.200
Then they heard more shouts.

41:31.240 --> 41:33.400
Long live King Edward.

41:34.040 --> 41:37.000
So now I am King.

41:37.000 --> 41:40.040
He said with tears in his eyes.

41:41.080 --> 41:42.840
Prince or King.

41:43.320 --> 41:44.600
Said Miles.

41:44.600 --> 41:46.600
You can stay with me tonight.

41:47.400 --> 41:50.120
We'll eat some food and rest.

41:51.480 --> 41:54.200
Miles's room at the inn was small.

41:54.840 --> 42:00.120
There was a bed, two chairs, a table and a wash stand.

42:00.120 --> 42:01.160
And a wash stand.

42:02.600 --> 42:05.800
Edward was very tired and fell on the bed.

42:07.000 --> 42:08.760
Call me when the food is ready.

42:09.400 --> 42:09.960
He said.

42:11.480 --> 42:15.880
Miles saw that the boy was cold and covered him with his jacket.

42:17.240 --> 42:18.520
Yes your majesty.

42:19.240 --> 42:20.760
Said Miles smiling.

42:22.120 --> 42:23.880
Miles went to get some food.

42:25.400 --> 42:27.720
Your banquet is ready your majesty.

42:27.720 --> 42:32.680
Edward washed his hands and sat down at the table.

42:34.040 --> 42:35.400
Miles sat down too.

42:36.600 --> 42:36.920
Wait.

42:37.640 --> 42:38.280
Said Edward.

42:39.240 --> 42:39.880
Stand up.

42:40.760 --> 42:41.960
I am your King.

42:42.920 --> 42:44.680
You must wait for my orders.

42:46.280 --> 42:47.400
Miles stood up.

42:49.000 --> 42:50.520
Now you can sit down.

42:52.120 --> 42:54.600
They were both hungry and started to eat.

42:55.400 --> 42:59.320
After dinner Edward looked at Miles and said.

43:00.200 --> 43:05.320
You are a courageous soldier of the King and you are good to me.

43:06.200 --> 43:09.960
Give me your sword and go down on your knee.

43:11.560 --> 43:15.720
With the side of the sword Edward touched Miles on the shoulder.

43:16.760 --> 43:17.480
Stand up.

43:18.040 --> 43:19.640
Sir Miles Hendon.

43:20.520 --> 43:23.000
Now you are one of my men.

43:24.680 --> 43:26.600
Miles stood up and laughed.

43:29.880 --> 43:34.840
Edward fell asleep with his head on the table and Miles took him to bed.

43:36.600 --> 43:37.720
Poor boy.

43:37.720 --> 43:38.280
He said.

43:39.160 --> 43:42.520
Perhaps he will be well again after a long sleep.

43:44.600 --> 43:47.320
That night Miles slept on the floor.

43:48.920 --> 43:52.920
The next morning Miles looked at the boy sleeping on the bed.

43:53.880 --> 43:55.640
The poor boy.

43:55.640 --> 43:56.280
He thought.

43:57.400 --> 44:04.120
He can sleep another hour and I'll go out to the market and buy him some new clothes.

44:05.880 --> 44:10.360
In the streets of London everyone was talking about the new King.

44:11.640 --> 44:13.240
Miles listened to them.

44:15.400 --> 44:19.560
People say the new King is mad.

44:20.840 --> 44:22.040
Said an old woman.

44:23.640 --> 44:26.200
He doesn't want to be King.

44:27.320 --> 44:29.720
He says he's a porper.

44:31.000 --> 44:34.360
Yes he says it's all a mistake.

44:35.320 --> 44:36.600
Said a young man.

44:37.800 --> 44:40.680
The poor young King is mad.

44:40.680 --> 44:43.000
Completely mad.

44:44.520 --> 44:46.280
Said another man laughing.

44:47.720 --> 44:49.480
Miles started thinking.

44:50.440 --> 44:54.280
Perhaps Edward is telling me the truth.

44:55.400 --> 44:57.640
Perhaps he is the King of England.

44:59.320 --> 45:02.680
He went back to the inn with the new clothes.

45:04.120 --> 45:08.520
When he got back to his room he was very surprised.

45:09.640 --> 45:11.480
Edward was gone.

45:13.240 --> 45:18.360
Miles immediately went to the man at the inn and asked.

45:19.240 --> 45:21.560
Where is the young boy?

45:21.560 --> 45:22.760
Oh dear.

45:23.560 --> 45:24.360
Said the man.

45:25.240 --> 45:27.400
Please don't get angry sir.

45:27.400 --> 45:29.160
Well where is he?

45:30.120 --> 45:32.280
Asked Miles angrily.

45:33.160 --> 45:34.520
Answer my question.

45:36.680 --> 45:38.920
The man's face became red.

45:39.560 --> 45:44.120
When you were away a man came and took the boy with him.

45:44.760 --> 45:45.320
A man?

45:46.200 --> 45:47.480
Said Miles.

45:47.480 --> 45:48.200
Surprised?

45:49.480 --> 45:50.360
Oh no.

45:51.480 --> 45:53.240
It was probably his father.

45:54.040 --> 45:55.000
The poor boy.

45:56.040 --> 45:56.840
Where did they go?

45:58.200 --> 46:01.080
Well sir they went towards Sothec.

46:01.800 --> 46:02.520
Said the man.

46:03.320 --> 46:06.200
And they disappeared in the crowd.

46:07.000 --> 46:08.040
Poor Edward.

46:08.840 --> 46:09.800
Said Miles.

46:10.600 --> 46:12.200
I must find him.

46:13.160 --> 46:19.880
He ran out of the inn and went towards Sothec, looking for his young friend.

46:21.320 --> 46:30.600
At the same time Edward had to follow John Canty through a forest outside London to an old barn.

46:31.800 --> 46:37.560
Inside the barn there were many beggars, thieves and vagabonds.

46:38.680 --> 46:41.000
John Canty knew most of them.

46:42.200 --> 46:45.800
What strange people.

46:46.760 --> 46:50.280
Thought Edward, looking at them silently.

46:51.320 --> 46:53.000
Where do they come from?

46:54.040 --> 46:56.360
Who's this boy John?

46:57.480 --> 47:00.760
Asked an old beggar with dirty clothes.

47:03.160 --> 47:04.280
He's my son.

47:05.240 --> 47:06.600
Said John Canty.

47:07.160 --> 47:07.400
No.

47:08.440 --> 47:09.720
Cried Edward.

47:09.720 --> 47:11.000
I'm not his son.

47:11.800 --> 47:13.960
I'm the king of England.

47:14.840 --> 47:17.640
Everyone in the barn started to laugh.

47:22.200 --> 47:26.680
An old beggar with long hair and no teeth.

47:26.680 --> 47:30.120
Said the king of England.

47:30.840 --> 47:33.880
He's the king of phones.

47:35.080 --> 47:37.320
And everyone laughed again.

47:41.960 --> 47:44.040
Edward was very sad.

47:45.240 --> 47:51.320
Soon everyone was saying unkind things to him and he wanted to cry.

47:52.200 --> 47:52.920
But he didn't.

47:54.120 --> 47:56.840
He went to sit in a corner and thought,

47:57.640 --> 47:59.640
Will Miles find me here?

48:01.080 --> 48:05.480
He was tired and hungry and he soon fell asleep.

48:06.440 --> 48:12.360
When Edward woke up the next morning, everyone in the barn was sleeping.

48:13.160 --> 48:20.680
He quickly and quietly opened the door and ran away into the forest.

48:21.880 --> 48:27.240
He ran all the way to the first village and stopped at the market.

48:28.280 --> 48:30.440
Suddenly he heard a voice.

48:31.080 --> 48:32.040
Edward.

48:32.040 --> 48:32.840
Edward.

48:33.960 --> 48:37.320
He turned around and saw Miles.

48:37.320 --> 48:40.200
Oh, how happy I am to see you.

48:40.840 --> 48:43.000
Said Edward, smiling.

48:43.800 --> 48:46.120
I looked for you everywhere.

48:46.920 --> 48:47.800
Said Miles.

48:49.000 --> 48:51.880
Edward told him about John Canty.

48:53.000 --> 48:57.800
And Miles told him what he heard at the market the day before.

48:58.680 --> 49:04.280
I believe you and now I know you're the king, your majesty.

49:05.000 --> 49:05.800
Said Miles.

49:07.160 --> 49:10.360
Let's go to my home, Hendon Hall.

49:11.320 --> 49:14.120
It's not far from Westminster Palace.

49:14.920 --> 49:20.520
And we can think of a plan to help you get back into the palace.

49:21.480 --> 49:24.200
I'm glad you believe me, Sir Miles.

49:24.920 --> 49:25.880
Said Edward.

49:28.600 --> 49:33.480
Chapter 6 The Life of a King

49:36.040 --> 49:43.480
It was morning and Tom woke up in a big, beautiful bed in Westminster Palace.

49:45.160 --> 49:50.520
When he opened his eyes, he saw two gentlemen by the side of his bed.

49:52.520 --> 49:53.560
Your majesty.

49:54.280 --> 49:55.960
Said the first gentleman.

49:56.760 --> 49:59.880
It's eight o'clock, your majesty.

50:00.680 --> 50:02.600
Said the second gentleman.

50:04.440 --> 50:04.840
What?

50:05.880 --> 50:06.600
Said Tom.

50:07.480 --> 50:09.720
Does your majesty wish to rise?

50:10.680 --> 50:12.280
Ask the first gentleman.

50:14.280 --> 50:17.560
Do you mean, do I want to get up?

50:18.680 --> 50:20.200
Yes, your majesty.

50:21.320 --> 50:22.920
Yes, I do.

50:23.960 --> 50:24.680
Said Tom.

50:26.200 --> 50:27.960
Where are my clothes?

50:30.280 --> 50:36.840
One gentleman brought Tom's underclothes into the room and gave them to a second gentleman.

50:37.640 --> 50:41.000
And the second gentleman gave them to a third gentleman.

50:41.720 --> 50:46.280
And the third gentleman helped Tom get into his underclothes.

50:47.720 --> 50:52.600
In this way, the gentleman dressed Tom in his expensive clothes.

50:53.480 --> 50:56.200
An hour later, he was ready.

50:57.800 --> 51:01.640
Tom went to another beautiful room to have breakfast.

51:03.400 --> 51:06.280
One servant brought the food into the room.

51:07.400 --> 51:09.480
He gave it to a second servant.

51:10.760 --> 51:13.800
The second servant gave it to a third servant.

51:14.600 --> 51:17.560
And the third servant put it on the table.

51:17.560 --> 51:22.440
A fourth servant put some food on Tom's plate.

51:23.960 --> 51:28.360
Two other servants stood behind Tom's chair and did nothing.

51:29.720 --> 51:32.280
The servants did everything for Tom.

51:33.880 --> 51:36.440
After breakfast, a servant said,

51:37.640 --> 51:41.640
Your majesty, Lord Hartford wants to speak to you.

51:43.320 --> 51:45.800
Lord Hartford came in and bowed.

51:46.760 --> 51:48.200
Is your majesty ready?

51:49.400 --> 51:52.040
The men are waiting in the council chamber.

51:53.880 --> 51:58.920
Tom went to the council chamber and sat in the king's gold chair.

52:00.760 --> 52:07.320
Men came, bowed and kissed his hand and read from long pieces of paper.

52:08.600 --> 52:12.680
It was very boring and it went on for hours.

52:13.480 --> 52:15.880
One man talked about money.

52:17.480 --> 52:24.280
There is no money, your majesty, because King Henry spent all of it.

52:25.080 --> 52:31.080
He built a lot of castles and wore expensive clothes and jewels.

52:31.880 --> 52:34.680
And his funeral was very expensive, too.

52:35.880 --> 52:39.880
You have 1,000 servants and you must pay them.

52:40.680 --> 52:43.480
Tom looked at the man and said,

52:44.680 --> 52:49.880
We can live in a small house with only 10 servants.

52:51.080 --> 52:55.880
There is a nice house in the city near Pudding Lane.

52:57.880 --> 53:03.880
Lord Hartford took Tom's arm gently and Tom stopped talking.

53:04.880 --> 53:06.880
Tom's face was red.

53:07.880 --> 53:09.880
Oh, when will this end?

53:10.880 --> 53:16.880
He thought, I want to play ball or swim in the river.

53:19.880 --> 53:24.880
He had lunch in the great dining room and the food was delicious.

53:25.880 --> 53:31.880
But he could not stop thinking about his friends and games at the river.

53:32.880 --> 53:39.880
After lunch, Tom went back to Prince Edward's room and sent everyone away.

53:40.880 --> 53:45.880
After a few minutes, a boy came in quietly.

53:46.880 --> 53:47.880
Who are you?

53:48.880 --> 53:49.880
Asked Tom.

53:50.880 --> 53:53.880
Oh, your majesty is really ill.

53:54.880 --> 53:55.880
Said the boy.

53:56.880 --> 53:57.880
I'm Humphrey Marlow.

53:57.880 --> 54:00.880
I'm Humphrey Marlow. I'm your whipping boy.

54:01.880 --> 54:03.880
My whipping boy?

54:04.880 --> 54:05.880
Cried Tom.

54:06.880 --> 54:07.880
Yes, your majesty.

54:08.880 --> 54:09.880
Said the boy.

54:10.880 --> 54:16.880
When you make mistakes during your Greek lesson, your teacher gets angry.

54:17.880 --> 54:23.880
But no one hits the Prince of Wales, so he hits me.

54:24.880 --> 54:25.880
That's my job.

54:25.880 --> 54:31.880
But now you're king and perhaps you won't study Greek anymore.

54:32.880 --> 54:37.880
Then I'll lose my job and my family will be hungry.

54:38.880 --> 54:40.880
We'll live on the streets.

54:41.880 --> 54:42.880
What?

54:43.880 --> 54:46.880
Tom looked at the boy and laughed loudly.

54:47.880 --> 54:48.880
Listen, Humphrey.

54:49.880 --> 54:54.880
I won't stop my studies and I'll make a lot of mistakes.

54:55.880 --> 55:00.880
They'll pay you more than before and you can work all your life.

55:01.880 --> 55:06.880
Oh, thank you, your majesty. You're very kind.

55:08.880 --> 55:14.880
Tom liked talking to Humphrey and learned a lot of things about Edward's life.

55:16.880 --> 55:21.880
Lord Hartford came for Tom and took him back to the council chamber.

55:22.880 --> 55:24.880
You're feeling better, your majesty.

55:25.880 --> 55:28.880
I can see it. You remember more.

55:29.880 --> 55:30.880
Said Lord Hartford.

55:31.880 --> 55:35.880
Do you remember where the great seal is?

55:36.880 --> 55:38.880
The great seal?

55:39.880 --> 55:40.880
Asked Tom.

55:41.880 --> 55:42.880
What's it like?

55:43.880 --> 55:44.880
Oh, dear.

55:45.880 --> 55:46.880
Thought the Lord.

55:47.880 --> 55:48.880
He's still not well.

55:48.880 --> 55:59.880
When they reached the council chamber, Tom had to sign Edward's name on a lot of papers all afternoon.

56:00.880 --> 56:03.880
The king's job was not easy.

56:04.880 --> 56:07.880
It was a long, boring afternoon.

56:08.880 --> 56:11.880
In the evening, there was another royal dinner.

56:12.880 --> 56:16.880
And after that, Tom finally went to bed.

56:18.880 --> 56:21.880
My clothes are beautiful.

56:22.880 --> 56:25.880
And the palace is splendid.

56:26.880 --> 56:27.880
He thought.

56:28.880 --> 56:31.880
The food is delicious.

56:32.880 --> 56:35.880
And now I'm never hungry.

56:36.880 --> 56:40.880
But I don't want to be king.

56:41.880 --> 56:43.880
Every day is the same.

56:44.880 --> 56:47.880
Putting lane is more fun.

56:49.880 --> 56:51.880
Listening activity.

56:53.880 --> 56:56.880
Hello, Humphrey.

56:57.880 --> 56:59.880
I'm Tom Canty.

57:00.880 --> 57:02.880
Where do you live?

57:03.880 --> 57:04.880
Hello, Tom.

57:05.880 --> 57:09.880
I live in a small house near the church.

57:10.880 --> 57:12.880
It's far from the palace.

57:13.880 --> 57:19.880
What time do you get up in the morning to come to work?

57:20.880 --> 57:27.880
I get up at half past six and have breakfast at seven.

57:28.880 --> 57:30.880
Then I come to work.

57:31.880 --> 57:35.880
How many brothers and sisters have you got?

57:36.880 --> 57:41.880
I've got two brothers and three sisters.

57:42.880 --> 57:48.880
My brother, James, works at the baker shop in Pudding Lane.

57:49.880 --> 57:52.880
What do you do in your free time?

57:53.880 --> 57:55.880
I don't have much free time.

57:56.880 --> 58:00.880
But on Sundays, I like playing ball.

58:06.880 --> 58:07.880
Chapter Seven.

58:08.880 --> 58:09.880
Hendon Hall.

58:11.880 --> 58:15.880
The next day, Edward rode with miles on his horse.

58:17.880 --> 58:20.880
In the afternoon, they came to a high hill.

58:22.880 --> 58:24.880
Miles stopped and said.

58:26.880 --> 58:28.880
Look, that's my home.

58:29.880 --> 58:30.880
Among the trees.

58:31.880 --> 58:36.880
It's a very big house with 50 rooms and 20 servants.

58:38.880 --> 58:42.880
They rode down the hill and passed through a big gate.

58:44.880 --> 58:46.880
This is Hendon Hall.

58:47.880 --> 58:49.880
Said Miles, happily.

58:50.880 --> 58:52.880
How glad I am to be home.

58:53.880 --> 58:55.880
My family will be so happy to see me.

58:56.880 --> 59:00.880
Miles ran into the house and Edward followed him.

59:02.880 --> 59:06.880
There was a young man with blonde hair at a long table.

59:07.880 --> 59:08.880
Hugh!

59:09.880 --> 59:10.880
Cried Miles.

59:11.880 --> 59:14.880
Aren't you happy to see me?

59:15.880 --> 59:16.880
Where's Father?

59:18.880 --> 59:24.880
The young man was unfriendly and looked at him with cold eyes.

59:26.880 --> 59:27.880
Who are you?

59:29.880 --> 59:30.880
Don't you know me?

59:31.880 --> 59:33.880
I'm your brother, Miles.

59:34.880 --> 59:36.880
I'm back from France after the war.

59:38.880 --> 59:40.880
My brother died in France.

59:41.880 --> 59:42.880
Said Hugh.

59:43.880 --> 59:45.880
We received a letter from his friend.

59:46.880 --> 59:47.880
No, no.

59:48.880 --> 59:49.880
I'm here.

59:50.880 --> 59:51.880
Said Miles.

59:52.880 --> 59:53.880
Where's my father?

59:54.880 --> 59:55.880
He'll know me.

59:56.880 --> 59:57.880
He's dead.

59:58.880 --> 59:59.880
Said Hugh.

59:59.880 --> 01:00:00.880
No.

01:00:00.880 --> 01:00:01.880
Poor Father.

01:00:02.880 --> 01:00:03.880
Cried Miles.

01:00:04.880 --> 01:00:06.880
Then call the servants.

01:00:07.880 --> 01:00:08.880
They'll know me.

01:00:09.880 --> 01:00:11.880
All the servants are new.

01:00:12.880 --> 01:00:13.880
Said Hugh.

01:00:14.880 --> 01:00:15.880
You sent them away.

01:00:16.880 --> 01:00:18.880
Cried Miles, angrily.

01:00:19.880 --> 01:00:21.880
Now I understand.

01:00:22.880 --> 01:00:27.880
You wrote the letter because you wanted the house and the money.

01:00:28.880 --> 01:00:33.880
But your plan won't work because Lady Edith will remember me.

01:00:34.880 --> 01:00:39.880
Lady Edith knows that Miles Hendon is dead.

01:00:40.880 --> 01:00:41.880
Said Hugh.

01:00:42.880 --> 01:00:44.880
She's my wife now.

01:00:46.880 --> 01:00:50.880
Miles was furious and ran across the room.

01:00:51.880 --> 01:00:53.880
You took my home and my land.

01:00:54.880 --> 01:00:55.880
You took my money.

01:00:56.880 --> 01:00:59.880
And you also took the woman I love.

01:01:00.880 --> 01:01:01.880
I'll kill you.

01:01:02.880 --> 01:01:08.880
He took Hugh by the shirt and pushed him against the wall angrily.

01:01:09.880 --> 01:01:10.880
Help!

01:01:10.880 --> 01:01:11.880
Help!

01:01:12.880 --> 01:01:13.880
Shouted Hugh.

01:01:14.880 --> 01:01:18.880
The servants ran into the room and pulled Miles from him.

01:01:19.880 --> 01:01:22.880
They took Miles and Edward away to prison.

01:01:23.880 --> 01:01:26.880
The prison was a terrible place.

01:01:27.880 --> 01:01:30.880
It was dark, cold and crowded.

01:01:31.880 --> 01:01:34.880
There were rats everywhere.

01:01:35.880 --> 01:01:40.880
Miles and Edward were chained together in a large noisy room.

01:01:41.880 --> 01:01:45.880
Some prisoners sang and others fought and shouted.

01:01:46.880 --> 01:01:50.880
A man hit a woman and almost killed her.

01:01:51.880 --> 01:01:53.880
Her face was covered with blood.

01:01:54.880 --> 01:01:56.880
Another woman cried loudly.

01:01:57.880 --> 01:01:59.880
What is the matter?

01:02:00.880 --> 01:02:01.880
Edward asked the woman.

01:02:02.880 --> 01:02:11.880
Tomorrow the soldiers are going to hang me because I stole some cheese.

01:02:12.880 --> 01:02:14.880
She said crying.

01:02:15.880 --> 01:02:18.880
Another sad young man spoke to Miles.

01:02:19.880 --> 01:02:24.880
They're going to hang me because I killed a deer in the king's park.

01:02:25.880 --> 01:02:26.880
But it's not true.

01:02:28.880 --> 01:02:30.880
Then he started to cry.

01:02:31.880 --> 01:02:35.880
Oh, prisons are sad, ugly place.

01:02:36.880 --> 01:02:37.880
Said Edward.

01:02:38.880 --> 01:02:41.880
No one helps these poor people.

01:02:42.880 --> 01:02:46.880
One day I will change these cruel laws.

01:02:47.880 --> 01:02:49.880
No one slept that night.

01:02:50.880 --> 01:02:55.880
The next day Miles and Edward were in front of the judge.

01:02:56.880 --> 01:02:59.880
Why are this man and this boy here?

01:03:00.880 --> 01:03:01.880
Asked the judge.

01:03:02.880 --> 01:03:05.880
Miles wanted to speak, but the judge said...

01:03:05.880 --> 01:03:06.880
Be quiet.

01:03:08.880 --> 01:03:10.880
He turned to Hugh and asked...

01:03:11.880 --> 01:03:14.880
Why did you bring them here, Mr Hendon?

01:03:15.880 --> 01:03:18.880
Hugh explained his story to the judge.

01:03:19.880 --> 01:03:24.880
Then Miles tried to speak, but the judge did not listen to him.

01:03:25.880 --> 01:03:28.880
The man must sit in the stalks for two hours.

01:03:29.880 --> 01:03:30.880
Said the judge.

01:03:31.880 --> 01:03:33.880
Then he and the boy can leave.

01:03:33.880 --> 01:03:35.880
Take them away immediately.

01:03:36.880 --> 01:03:37.880
No!

01:03:38.880 --> 01:03:39.880
cried Edward.

01:03:40.880 --> 01:03:41.880
He's my servant.

01:03:42.880 --> 01:03:44.880
You don't know what you're doing.

01:03:45.880 --> 01:03:46.880
Be quiet, boy.

01:03:47.880 --> 01:03:49.880
Or the soldiers will hit you.

01:03:50.880 --> 01:03:51.880
Said the judge.

01:03:53.880 --> 01:03:55.880
The soldiers put Miles into the stalks.

01:03:57.880 --> 01:04:02.880
Some people stopped and looked, and others threw bad eggs at him.

01:04:04.880 --> 01:04:08.880
Edward stood in front of Miles and tried to protect him.

01:04:09.880 --> 01:04:11.880
The people laughed and said...

01:04:12.880 --> 01:04:14.880
He's a courageous boy!

01:04:15.880 --> 01:04:17.880
And he loves his friend.

01:04:19.880 --> 01:04:26.880
At the end of the two hours, the soldiers took Miles out of the stalks and he was free.

01:04:27.880 --> 01:04:29.880
He looked at Edward and said...

01:04:30.880 --> 01:04:34.880
Now we can finally go to London.

01:04:38.880 --> 01:04:41.880
Chapter 8. The New King

01:04:43.880 --> 01:04:49.880
When Miles and Edward arrived in London, they saw a crowd of people in the streets.

01:04:50.880 --> 01:04:56.880
There were flags on all of the buildings and a lot of noise everywhere.

01:04:57.880 --> 01:05:04.880
It was the 19th of February and the next day was Coronation Day.

01:05:05.880 --> 01:05:08.880
Everyone was happy and excited.

01:05:10.880 --> 01:05:15.880
Miles and Edward were in the big crowd and they soon got lost.

01:05:17.880 --> 01:05:19.880
They could not find each other anymore.

01:05:20.880 --> 01:05:25.880
Poor Edward was cold, hungry and alone.

01:05:27.880 --> 01:05:36.880
Tom, on the other hand, was beginning to enjoy the royal palace, the beautiful new clothes and the good food.

01:05:37.880 --> 01:05:42.880
Everyone bowed to him and listened to him, and he liked this.

01:05:43.880 --> 01:05:51.880
During his first days at the palace, he thought about his mother, sisters and Edward.

01:05:52.880 --> 01:06:00.880
But as the days passed, he almost forgot about them because he liked his wonderful new life.

01:06:01.880 --> 01:06:04.880
He was happy and comfortable.

01:06:06.880 --> 01:06:10.880
The next morning was the 20th of February, Coronation Day.

01:06:12.880 --> 01:06:13.880
Tom thought...

01:06:14.880 --> 01:06:19.880
Today, I'm going to become King of England.

01:06:20.880 --> 01:06:26.880
I'm going to wear splendid new clothes and jewels in the parade.

01:06:27.880 --> 01:06:30.880
Oh, this is wonderful!

01:06:32.880 --> 01:06:40.880
Soon, Tom Canty was splendidly dressed and riding a tall horse in the royal parade.

01:06:41.880 --> 01:06:48.880
Behind him there were lords and rich gentlemen dressed in their best clothes.

01:06:49.880 --> 01:06:56.880
There was music in the air and thousands of happy people in the streets of London.

01:06:57.880 --> 01:07:00.880
Hurrah for the new King of England!

01:07:01.880 --> 01:07:02.880
They shouted.

01:07:03.880 --> 01:07:08.880
Tom smiled and often threw new coins to the people.

01:07:09.880 --> 01:07:11.880
He felt important.

01:07:12.880 --> 01:07:16.880
Suddenly, he saw his mother in the big crowd.

01:07:17.880 --> 01:07:23.880
She touched his leg and cried, Oh, my dear child!

01:07:24.880 --> 01:07:26.880
A soldier pushed her away.

01:07:27.880 --> 01:07:34.880
Tom looked at her and said, I don't know you, woman!

01:07:35.880 --> 01:07:40.880
His mother was very sad and disappeared in the crowd.

01:07:41.880 --> 01:07:44.880
After a moment, Tom thought,

01:07:45.880 --> 01:07:49.880
Oh, no! What did I say?

01:07:51.880 --> 01:07:56.880
He felt terrible and suddenly he was unhappy.

01:07:58.880 --> 01:08:04.880
The royal parade continued down the streets of London to Westminster Abbey.

01:08:05.880 --> 01:08:11.880
The church was full of people and beautifully decorated for the great day.

01:08:12.880 --> 01:08:21.880
At last, the Archbishop of Canterbury took the crown of England and lifted it over Tom's head.

01:08:22.880 --> 01:08:24.880
Everyone was silent.

01:08:25.880 --> 01:08:34.880
Suddenly, a young boy with no shoes and old dirty clothes ran into the church.

01:08:35.880 --> 01:08:38.880
You're not the king! I'm the king!

01:08:39.880 --> 01:08:40.880
He cried.

01:08:41.880 --> 01:08:45.880
Everyone was surprised and the people looked at each other.

01:08:46.880 --> 01:08:47.880
What's happening?

01:08:48.880 --> 01:08:49.880
Asked one gentleman.

01:08:51.880 --> 01:08:54.880
Who's that pauper? What does he want?

01:08:55.880 --> 01:08:56.880
Asked a lady.

01:08:58.880 --> 01:09:02.880
Lord Hartford quickly said, Soldiers, stop this boy.

01:09:03.880 --> 01:09:07.880
Edward and Tom looked at each other for a moment.

01:09:08.880 --> 01:09:09.880
No!

01:09:10.880 --> 01:09:11.880
Said Tom.

01:09:12.880 --> 01:09:13.880
Don't touch him!

01:09:14.880 --> 01:09:16.880
He is the real king!

01:09:18.880 --> 01:09:20.880
Everyone was confused.

01:09:21.880 --> 01:09:26.880
Lord Hartford looked at the two boys and said, look at their faces!

01:09:27.880 --> 01:09:29.880
They're identical!

01:09:30.880 --> 01:09:32.880
But who is our king?

01:09:33.880 --> 01:09:36.880
He is the real king!

01:09:37.880 --> 01:09:39.880
Said Tom, smiling at Edward.

01:09:41.880 --> 01:09:43.880
Ask him about the great seal.

01:09:44.880 --> 01:09:45.880
Very well?

01:09:46.880 --> 01:09:47.880
Said Lord Hartford.

01:09:48.880 --> 01:09:52.880
Only the real king can answer this question.

01:09:53.880 --> 01:09:55.880
Where's the great seal?

01:09:56.880 --> 01:10:04.880
Edward immediately said, look inside the old Italian suit of armour in my room.

01:10:05.880 --> 01:10:07.880
The great seal's there.

01:10:08.880 --> 01:10:14.880
Lord Hartford sent Lord John to look for the great seal in the palace.

01:10:15.880 --> 01:10:22.880
When he returned, he said, I found the great seal. Here it is.

01:10:23.880 --> 01:10:27.880
The pauper is right. He is the king.

01:10:29.880 --> 01:10:35.880
The archbishop of Canterbury put the crown of England on Edward's young head.

01:10:37.880 --> 01:10:40.880
Everyone in the church stood up and cheered.

01:10:41.880 --> 01:10:44.880
Long live young king Edward!

01:10:46.880 --> 01:10:49.880
Tom looked at the great seal and said,

01:10:50.880 --> 01:10:56.880
I used it to crack nuts. I didn't know it was the great seal.

01:10:57.880 --> 01:11:03.880
He used the great seal of England to crack nuts.

01:11:04.880 --> 01:11:06.880
Said Lord Hartford loudly.

01:11:07.880 --> 01:11:08.880
How funny!

01:11:12.880 --> 01:11:16.880
All the great lords laughed and laughed.

01:11:17.880 --> 01:11:24.880
The great ceremony ended and Edward became King Edward VI.

01:11:25.880 --> 01:11:31.880
The next day, Miles went to see his friend, King Edward VI.

01:11:32.880 --> 01:11:40.880
The young king was happy to see Sir Miles, who told him more about his problems with his brother Hugh.

01:11:41.880 --> 01:11:44.880
You were kind and helped me Sir Miles.

01:11:44.880 --> 01:11:46.880
Said the young king.

01:11:47.880 --> 01:11:49.880
Now I will help you.

01:11:50.880 --> 01:11:54.880
You can go back to Hendon House because it's yours again.

01:11:55.880 --> 01:11:59.880
Your brother Hugh will give everything back to you.

01:12:01.880 --> 01:12:02.880
Thank you, King Edward.

01:12:03.880 --> 01:12:05.880
Said Sir Miles, happily.

01:12:07.880 --> 01:12:11.880
King Edward VI was a very good and kind king.

01:12:11.880 --> 01:12:16.880
Because for those few days he was a pauper.

01:12:17.880 --> 01:12:22.880
He knew his people and understood their problems.

01:12:23.880 --> 01:12:29.880
Tom Canty was the king's best friend and lived in Westminster Palace.

01:12:30.880 --> 01:12:36.880
King Edward gave Tom's mother and sisters a lovely house in the country.

01:12:36.880 --> 01:12:41.880
And no one saw John Canty again.

01:12:42.880 --> 01:12:47.880
King Edward VI died when he was only 16.

01:12:48.880 --> 01:12:53.880
Tom was very sad and left Westminster Palace.

01:12:54.880 --> 01:12:58.880
He went to live with his mother and sisters in the country.

01:12:59.880 --> 01:13:03.880
Everyone remembered the young king for a long time.

01:13:03.880 --> 01:13:06.880
Because he loved all of his people.

01:13:07.880 --> 01:13:10.880
The rich and the poor.

